        public void add(co.cask.cdap.proto.id.NamespaceId namespace,
       String artifactName,
       com.google.common.io.InputSupplier<? extends InputStream> artifactContents,
       @Nullable
       String artifactVersion,
       @Nullable
       Set<co.cask.cdap.proto.artifact.ArtifactRange> parentArtifacts,
       @Nullable
       Set<PluginClass> additionalPlugins)
         throws co.cask.cdap.common.ArtifactAlreadyExistsException,
                co.cask.cdap.common.BadRequestException,
                IOException,
                co.cask.cdap.common.UnauthenticatedException,
                co.cask.cdap.common.ArtifactRangeNotFoundException,
                co.cask.cdap.security.spi.authorization.UnauthorizedException
        Add an artifact.
        Parameters:
        namespace - the namespace to add the artifact to
        artifactName - the name of the artifact to add
        artifactContents - an input supplier for the contents of the artifact
        artifactVersion - the version of the artifact to add. If null, the version will be derived from the manifest of the artifact
        parentArtifacts - the set of artifacts this artifact extends
        additionalPlugins - the set of plugins contained in the artifact that cannot be determined through jar inspection. This set should include any classes that are plugins but could not be annotated as such. For example, 3rd party classes like jdbc drivers fall into this category.
        Throws:
        co.cask.cdap.common.ArtifactAlreadyExistsException - if the artifact already exists
        co.cask.cdap.common.BadRequestException - if the request is invalid. For example, if the artifact name or version is invalid
        co.cask.cdap.common.ArtifactRangeNotFoundException - if the parent artifacts do not exist
        IOException - if a network error occurred
        co.cask.cdap.common.UnauthenticatedException - if the request is not authorized successfully in the gateway server
        co.cask.cdap.security.spi.authorization.UnauthorizedException
